Turkish President Erdoğan Rejects Proposals for Palestinian Displacement from Gaza

### English Text Summary:
Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdoğan stated that any proposal to displace Palestinians from Gaza is "worthless" to Turkey, emphasizing the country's commitment to supporting the establishment of a Palestinian state based on the 1967 borders. In a post on his official social media account, Erdoğan asserted that Gaza belongs to its residents and that Palestine is for the Palestinians. He condemned any new displacement of Palestinians, highlighting the ongoing plight of millions of refugees who hold keys to their ancestral homes. Erdoğan reiterated that there is no alternative to a two-state solution and pledged Turkey's unwavering support for the Palestinian cause.

